<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8"/>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
<title>Ropa-Sci TUI Roadmap</title>
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body {
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
    background: #0f0f11;
    color: #e2e0d8;
    padding: 2rem 1.25rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }
  .container { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }

  /* Header */
  .header { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .project-name {
    font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #fff; margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .project-name span { color: #7F77DD; }
  .sub { font-size: 13px; color: #888780; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .meta-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; }
  .mpill {
    font-size: 11px; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid #2a2a2e; color: #888780;
  }

  /* Week bar */
  .week-bar { display: flex; gap: 3px; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .wc { flex: 1; height: 5px; border-radius: 3px; }
  .legend-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .leg { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px; font-size: 11px; color: #888780; }
  .ld { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; }

  /* Phase cards */
  .phase {
    border: 1px solid #222227; border-radius: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem; overflow: hidden;
  }
  .phdr {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
    padding: 0.8rem 1rem; cursor: pointer; user-select: none;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  .phdr:hover { background: #18181c; }
  .wtag {
    font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; padding: 2px 9px;
    border-radius: 999px; flex-shrink: 0; white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .ptitle { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; color: #e2e0d8; flex: 1; }
  .role-badge {
    font-size: 10px; padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 4px; flex-shrink: 0;
    background: #1a2535; color: #6ea8d8; border: 1px solid #263447;
  }
  .role-star { color: #f0c040; }
  .chv { font-size: 11px; color: #555; flex-shrink: 0; }

  .pbody { display: none; padding: 0 1rem 0.85rem; }
  .pbody.open { display: block; }

  ul { list-style: none; margin-top: 0.4rem; }
  li {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 8px;
    padding: 6px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1e1e22;
    font-size: 12px; color: #9a9890; line-height: 1.55;
  }
  li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .dot { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 4px; }
  .you { color: #dbd9d0; font-weight: 500; }
  code {
    font-family: "SF Mono", "Consolas", monospace;
    font-size: 11px; background: #1e1e22; padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px; color: #c8b4f0;
  }
  .bg {
    font-size: 10px; padding: 1px 6px; border-radius: 3px;
    margin-left: auto; flex-shrink: 0; white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .bui  { background: #1e1a35; color: #a49de0; border: 1px solid #2d2750; }
  .bco  { background: #0f2218; color: #4caf84; border: 1px solid #1a3a28; }
  .bte  { background: #0d1e30; color: #5a9fd4; border: 1px solid #182e44; }

  /* Sync box */
  .sync {
    border: 1px solid #2a2a2e; border-radius: 8px;
    background: #15151a; padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    margin: 0.75rem 0; font-size: 12px; color: #888780; line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .sync strong { color: #e2e0d8; }

  .footer { margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: 11px; color: #444; text-align: center; }

  /* Color palette */
  .w1c { background: #7F77DD; }
  .w2c { background: #1D9E75; }
  .w3c { background: #BA7517; }
  .w4c { background: #D85A30; }
  .w5c { background: #378ADD; }
  .w6c,.w7c,.w8c { background: #444440; }

  .tw1 { background: #231f3d; color: #a49de0; border: 1px solid #312b57; }
  .tw2 { background: #0d2218; color: #3aae7a; border: 1px solid #193325; }
  .tw3 { background: #2a1c08; color: #cc8c30; border: 1px solid #3d2a0d; }
  .tw4 { background: #2e1409; color: #e07050; border: 1px solid #441f0e; }
  .tw5 { background: #0d1e30; color: #5a9fd4; border: 1px solid #182e44; }
  .tw6,.tw7,.tw8 { background: #1a1a1e; color: #888780; border: 1px solid #2a2a2e; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">

  <div class="header">
    <div class="project-name"><span>ROPA</span>-SCI — TUI Frontend Roadmap</div>
    <div class="sub">Your personal 8-week build plan · Jezreel (jmomoh) · Frontend Developer</div>
    <div class="meta-row">
      <span class="mpill">Go + Bubbletea + Lipgloss</span>
      <span class="mpill">Rock · Paper · Scissors</span>
      <span class="mpill">5-person team</span>
      <span class="mpill">WebSocket multiplayer</span>
      <span class="mpill">March – May 2026</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="week-bar">
    <div class="wc w1c"></div><div class="wc w2c"></div><div class="wc w3c"></div>
    <div class="wc w4c"></div><div class="wc w5c"></div><div class="wc w6c"></div>
    <div class="wc w7c"></div><div class="wc w8c"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="legend-row">
    <div class="leg"><div class="ld w1c"></div>Wk 1</div>
    <div class="leg"><div class="ld w2c"></div>Wk 2</div>
    <div class="leg"><div class="ld w3c"></div>Wk 3</div>
    <div class="leg"><div class="ld w4c"></div>Wk 4</div>
    <div class="leg"><div class="ld w5c"></div>Wk 5</div>
    <div class="leg"><div class="ld w6c"></div>Wks 6–8</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Week 1 -->
  <div class="phase">
    <div class="phdr" onclick="tog(1)">
      <span class="wtag tw1">Week 1</span>
      <span class="ptitle">Setup + team alignment</span>
      <span class="role-badge">Consulted</span>
      <span class="chv" id="c1">▶</span>
    </div>
    <div class="pbody" id="b1">
      <ul>
        <li><div class="dot w1c"></div><span class="you">Create your repo <code>ropa-sci-frontend/</code>, set up <code>go.mod</code>, push to GitHub<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w1c"></div><span class="you">Install: <code>go get github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea</code>, <code>lipgloss</code>, <code>bubbles</code><span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w1c"></div><span class="you">Build a Hello World Bubbletea app — just text + press q to quit. Prove it works.<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w1c"></div><span>Agree with backend (Micheal + Radiance) on shared Go structs: <code>Player</code>, <code>Move</code>, <code>GameResult</code><span class="bg bco">sync</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w1c"></div><span>Agree on WebSocket message format now — save pain later<span class="bg bco">sync</span></span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Week 2 -->
  <div class="phase">
    <div class="phdr" onclick="tog(2)">
      <span class="wtag tw2">Week 2</span>
      <span class="ptitle">Main menu screen</span>
      <span class="role-badge"><span class="role-star">★</span> Responsible</span>
      <span class="chv" id="c2">▶</span>
    </div>
    <div class="pbody" id="b2">
      <ul>
        <li><div class="dot w2c"></div><span class="you">Build the main menu: "ROPA-SCI" title banner + 3 options (Single Player / Multiplayer / Quit)<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w2c"></div><span class="you">Keyboard navigation: ↑ ↓ move cursor, Enter selects, q quits<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w2c"></div><span class="you">Wire up multi-screen routing skeleton: Menu → Game → Result → back to Menu<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w2c"></div><span class="you">Style with Lipgloss: bordered box, color title, padded layout — consistent look<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Week 3 -->
  <div class="phase">
    <div class="phdr" onclick="tog(3)">
      <span class="wtag tw3">Week 3</span>
      <span class="ptitle">ASCII art + game screen</span>
      <span class="role-badge"><span class="role-star">★</span> Responsible</span>
      <span class="chv" id="c3">▶</span>
    </div>
    <div class="pbody" id="b3">
      <ul>
        <li><div class="dot w3c"></div><span class="you">Draw Rock / Paper / Scissors ASCII art — one per move choice<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w3c"></div><span class="you">Game screen: player picks move → both choices shown side-by-side in ASCII<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w3c"></div><span class="you">Result display: WIN (green) / LOSE (red) / TIE (yellow) with Lipgloss color<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w3c"></div><span class="you">Best-of-three score tracker: Round 1 ✓  Round 2 ✗  Round 3 …<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w3c"></div><span class="you">End-of-match screen: Play Again / Main Menu / Quit<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Week 4 -->
  <div class="phase">
    <div class="phdr" onclick="tog(4)">
      <span class="wtag tw4">Week 4</span>
      <span class="ptitle">Single-player mode (wire AI)</span>
      <span class="role-badge"><span class="role-star">★</span> Responsible</span>
      <span class="chv" id="c4">▶</span>
    </div>
    <div class="pbody" id="b4">
      <ul>
        <li><div class="dot w4c"></div><span>Backend (Micheal/Radiance) delivers random AI move function<span class="bg bco">backend</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w4c"></div><span class="you">Wire AI into your UI: player picks → AI picks → show result screen<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w4c"></div><span class="you">"AI is thinking…" spinner (0.5s delay using <code>tea.Tick</code>)<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w4c"></div><span class="you">Full best-of-three loop working end-to-end in single-player<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w4c"></div><span class="you">Self-test: play 20 rounds, fix edge cases — ties, score reset, early quit<span class="bg bte">test</span></span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sync">
    🔗 <strong>Mid-project sync — end of Week 4</strong><br>
    Demo your working single-player TUI to the whole team. Backend confirms WebSocket message format. Lock the API contract before Week 5. Don't skip this — a week of integration pain starts here if you do.
  </div>

  <!-- Week 5 -->
  <div class="phase">
    <div class="phdr" onclick="tog(5)">
      <span class="wtag tw5">Week 5</span>
      <span class="ptitle">Multiplayer UI (WebSocket)</span>
      <span class="role-badge"><span class="role-star">★</span> Responsible</span>
      <span class="chv" id="c5">▶</span>
    </div>
    <div class="pbody" id="b5">
      <ul>
        <li><div class="dot w5c"></div><span>Backend delivers WebSocket server<span class="bg bco">backend</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w5c"></div><span class="you">"Waiting for opponent…" screen with live spinner<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w5c"></div><span class="you">Go WebSocket client: opponent's move arrives as a <code>tea.Msg</code> into your Update()<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w5c"></div><span class="you">Handle all network states: connecting / in-game / opponent disconnected<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w5c"></div><span class="you">Multiplayer best-of-three end-to-end with a real second terminal<span class="bg bte">test</span></span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Week 6 -->
  <div class="phase">
    <div class="phdr" onclick="tog(6)">
      <span class="wtag tw6">Week 6</span>
      <span class="ptitle">Integration testing</span>
      <span class="role-badge">Consulted</span>
      <span class="chv" id="c6">▶</span>
    </div>
    <div class="pbody" id="b6">
      <ul>
        <li><div class="dot w6c"></div><span>QA runs cross-machine multiplayer tests<span class="bg bte">QA</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w6c"></div><span class="you">Fix all UI bugs found: crashes, frozen screens, display glitches<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w6c"></div><span class="you">Test on different terminal sizes — layout must not break on small terminals<span class="bg bte">test</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w6c"></div><span>Validate: both players always see the same game state simultaneously<span class="bg bte">test</span></span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Week 7 -->
  <div class="phase">
    <div class="phdr" onclick="tog(7)">
      <span class="wtag tw7">Week 7</span>
      <span class="ptitle">Bug fixes + polish</span>
      <span class="role-badge">Responsible</span>
      <span class="chv" id="c7">▶</span>
    </div>
    <div class="pbody" id="b7">
      <ul>
        <li><div class="dot w7c"></div><span class="you">Fix all bugs reported from Week 6 testing<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w7c"></div><span class="you">Polish: consistent colors, aligned ASCII, smooth screen transitions<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w7c"></div><span class="you">Add a help screen: press <code>?</code> anytime to see all keybinds<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w7c"></div><span class="you">Write unit tests for <code>Update()</code>: score logic + screen transitions (≥80% target from charter)<span class="bg bte">test</span></span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Week 8 -->
  <div class="phase">
    <div class="phdr" onclick="tog(8)">
      <span class="wtag tw8">Week 8</span>
      <span class="ptitle">Documentation + release</span>
      <span class="role-badge">Accountable</span>
      <span class="chv" id="c8">▶</span>
    </div>
    <div class="pbody" id="b8">
      <ul>
        <li><div class="dot w8c"></div><span class="you">Write README: install, build, run — single-player and multiplayer clearly explained<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w8c"></div><span class="you">Add a terminal GIF or screenshot to README — makes your GitHub portfolio shine<span class="bg bui">you</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w8c"></div><span>Final peer review + team sign-off (all 5 members)<span class="bg bco">team</span></span></li>
        <li><div class="dot w8c"></div><span>Push final clean version — tidy commit history, no debug leftovers<span class="bg bco">team</span></span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="footer">Click any week to expand · ★ = your heaviest delivery weeks: 2, 3, 4, 5 · Built for jmomoh @ Learn2Earn</div>

</div>
<script>
function tog(n) {
  var b = document.getElementById('b' + n);
  var c = document.getElementById('c' + n);
  var open = b.classList.toggle('open');
  c.textContent = open ? '▼' : '▶';
}
</script>
</body>
</html>
